description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 Equality, Diversity and Inclusion Administrator&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced administrator with a passion for equality and diversity?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a new full time administrator to help with administration of our Equality, Diversity and Inclusion strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So who are we? We are People and Organisational Development Directorate who support the Trust to meet and develop its public sector duty to promote workforce equality to enhance patient and staff experience and quality of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful postholder will need to be able to work under pressure and meet tight deadlines with excellent problem solving skills. We expect that you will be proactive in working collaboratively with other departments and the staff networks. You will need to be confident working with detail, taking accurate minutes, updating project plans, using online platforms and producing high quality administrative documents with attention to detail. You will need to be confident to use Microsoft powerpoint, excel, word and MS teams effectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can consider compressed hours, agile homeworking and are very happy to discuss other flexible working options.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on Friday 20 November 2020 and will be conducted virtually.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The closing date of this advert is Friday 6th November.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Olayinka Iwu Olayinka.Iwu@Nhs.Net&lt;/p&gt;
